VSennheiser RS 180 Wireless Headset -ALMOST Perfect
p30
sg5
VHaving previously owned the earlier RS 160, I knew the quality of these "cans."  The RS 160 didn't have enough RANGE to cover my home, and wanted the increased range and AGC (automatic gain control) to tame loud passages.  I am THRILLED with the new RS 180!  It covers my whole home and out into the yard for a little distance.  You'll never get the rated 100 metre range unless the transmitter and receiver are both outside and in the clear, but the range of this pair is very adequate!Only complaint I had was that the control buttons are FLAT on the edge of the right earphone.  THAT WAS EASILY SOLVED by mixing up a small batch of acrylic polymer resin, and applying ONE DROP to the volume + and volume - buttons.  After it dried in about an hour, it left those buttons with a raised "bump" that my fingers can easily find.  The on/off/standby button is between the volume buttons, so it is now easy to find with my fingers also.  With this easy modification, I give this headset a solid 5 STARS.  Too bad Sennheiser didn't do this at the factory, but it is very easy to do at homeThe sound of this headset is outstanding.  It fits comfortably on the ears for hours of use without discomfort.  The AGC works VERY WELL indeed.  The two AAA NiMh rechargable batteries will run the cans for 24 hours, and all I have to do to recharge them is to "hang" the headset on the transmitter.  Nothing to plug in.  When, in time, the batteries are exhausted, I can simply purchase replacements at the grocery store and change them out in less than a minute.I was SO PLEASED with the RS 180, that I purchased a second pair to carry with me to field locations.
