VGood Headphones
p57
sg5
VThese headphones were a replacement for a set of 5 year old Sennheiser RS120 headphones that we wore out (which had in turn replaced a cheaper set of headphones).  Our 97 yr old mother uses them to watch TV.Positives: The sound quality is much better than the 120's.  Also the RS180's fit on her head better than the RS120s which were always loose (and would fall off when she looked down quickly).  In my opinion The RS180s are worth the extra $.  I would definitely recommend these.Negatives: Our most major complaint is the design of the controls.  The RS120 model used one wheel for on/off and volume control.  The RS180's uses three small flush-mounted buttons for up/down volume with the On/Off button BETWEEN the volume buttons!  All three buttons are in a 1 1/2 by 3/8 inch space with almost no way to feel which button you want.  Not an easy task for any fingers, much less older fingers.  We partially solved that by putting a small foam pad on the on/off button (thus separating the volume buttons).  But why should we have had to invent a solution?  One other complaint, both the base unit and the headphones automatically shut off when the headphones are being recharged.  Then both must be turned back on to use the headphones.  The On/Off button on the base unit is very, very small and not easy to see if a person has vision problems and cannot be easily felt.  A light flashes slowly when the base unit is on, but is dark when it is off.  In an effort to make the units sleek, there is almost no tactile or color differential to highlight any button on either the headphones or the base. Again, we invented a solution which works for us, but the whole headphone unit seems to be designed more for appearance than ease of use.  The whole unit does look nice, however.  I'd rate it a "C-" in ease of use and an "A" in sound quality.
