VTop notch, if latency is of no concern
p63
sg5
VI've been using the Sennheiser TR120 wireless headphones for several years, plugged into my M-Audio fast-track for practicing and playing guitar along with iTunes, and also for recording.  They worked really well, but were definitely lacking in sound quality, and had a handful of other shortcomings.  I decided to spend more. A LOT more.  The RS 180s, once set up, sound fantastic.  Really.  They are very high-quality.  However, in order to move that much more sound data through the air, more time is needed to get from point A to point B, which means latency.  Extremely noticeable latency.  Probably about 1/3 of a second.  That may not sound like much, but when you're playing 32nd notes on a guitar, what you're playing gets to your ears 4 notes later than you played it, making these completely unusable for the application. For those listening to passive sound sources (stereo, iPod, etc) you can't go wrong.  For those watching TV, as long as your TV or other equipment has delay compensation, you'll be fine, too.  For active applications such as gaming or playing an instrument, however, these are out of the question.  A real shame.
