VI got this because I didn't want to disturb my wife when she was sleeping in the bedroom and I was watching a movie in the living room. Once I got the hang of it, it works perfectly. I'm used to listening to 5.1 channel stereo on speakers, and so it's a bit of a comedown to hear only stereo, but the placement of the speaker stage is really good. This particular model tends to emphasize the center channel, which is good for me because I usually find dialogue is mixed too soft against music. So wearing these, I hear the dialogue much better than with the speakers. I think there's another similar model that is made to emphasize the "feel" of a five-speaker system.I find that in my house I can walk ANYWHERE and get a clean signal. I imagine those who complained about a hum or buzz or something else have some location issue, like lots of walls, florescent lighting, or a conflict with the frequency the headphones operate at. I use a DECT 6 wireless phone system, and have a dual-band wifi network in the house, and NEITHER interferes with the clear sound.One last thing, which is amazing: these headphones (which surround the ear) are actually comfortable enough to watch a double-feature (okay, maybe taking a short break in between). I think these may be the most physically comfortable headphones I've ever worn.
