VSound Quality-I've had the priveledge of hearing some the best headphones on the market both wired and wireless and I can honestly say, when it comes to sound quality, you will not find a wireless headphone that's better. Sure Sennheiser's HD650 sound better to me, but can they grab a snack from the kitchen, or allow me to keep my little rugrat out of trouble while I can still hear the movie or music I'm listening to clear as the sky is blue?... Nope, they can't. IMHO for under (...) you would be hard pressed to find a headphone, even wired,  that you could tell a noticeable in sound quality difference over the RS 180's if you aren't a headphone aficionado.Transmission-The move to KLEER technology is a godsend, no more crackles and pops found in the wireless headphones of yesteryear or for that matter yeasterday. This is especially important these days with so many possible sources of interference in our homes.Comfort-What's not to like about plush earpads, a well padded headband, and just enough pressure on the sides of your head to keep them snug, but hardly notice they are on?Noteworthy Features-I have always had difficulty hearing dialogue in movies, especially whispering...fortuneatley these headphones automatically adjust volume levels when speech volume is lowered so that speech intelligbility is always maintained. It also has balance control for those of us who need it louder in one ear instead of the other.The buttons on the side are an improvement over the 120,130,and 140 models becuase you can lay down with them on and not accidently adjust the volume. They do have one flaw though, who decided that putting the power button between volume up and down?...He/she was not a smart person. The fact that they are flat buttons isn't ideal either, however I got use to finding the buttons pretty quickly.Additionally, like the old RS 120,130,and 140 models, the batteries are recharged when the headset is placed back on its stand after use, all ready to go next time you want to use them.I can sit here and tell you how much I love the Sennheiser RS 180, which is obvious by now, but at the end of the day you need to know what the consensus opinion on these headphones are and not just take the opinion of one man to heart. So, I will share with you my secret to buying a new pair of headphones.  It's (...), which provides consensus reviews for you...no more searching the internet for user and professional reviews alike. I don't know why there aren't any other sites like this because I've always had difficulty finding enough good reviews on headphones, especially new products like the RS 180's. It not only makes finding reviews easier, but summarizes them all for me...more time for me to enjoy the headphones and less time shopping for them Hooray!
