Vgreat sound quality
p245
sg5
VUpdate #2:  Still going strong after 20 months of use.  We use these daily and they are still going strong and the original Eneloop batteries are still holding a charge.  No issues after almost 2 years of near daily use.UPDATE:After owning these for close to 2 months, I have to say these headphones have changed my life.  My home theater system is a force to be reckoned with, with 5.1 speakers perfectly balanced, a 120" pull down screen and 1080p Epson 8350 projector.  But listening to movies with these headphones is really the best way to experience movies.  They are nice for music, no doubt, but having 2 pair of these (for my wife and I), no wires, no static, perfect sound, is just spectacular.  Movies just come alive.  Of course, you can do the same with any good headphones and 20 feet of knotted cables, and everyone has to sit still or you yank the other persons' headphones off their head...but doing it without wires is obviously the way to go.  The freedom to move around while hearing perfect sound is just great.I'd recommend these to anyone with a home theater system, anyone over 50 who is starting to have hearing problems, anyone who misses the dialog in movies and TV shows, or anyone who wants to enjoy music and movies.  Okay...I recommend these to anyone who can afford them.Again, I have a lot of wireless going on in my living room, and have never had a problem with a single lost syllable.  Even watching streaming movies over wifi with the PS3 right next to the transmitter has not been a problem.  I have had zero issues with these after 2 months of use.  I even dropped one pair once (my heart skipped a beat) but nothing happened to it.I increased my review to 5 stars, even with the terrible button placement for volume and power.Here is my original review:I have two other open Sennheiser headphones:  HD555 and HD518.  My favorite are (were) the HD555, for their crisp sound.  The HD518 have more bass, but I think it sounds fake or muffled.  Anyway, the RS180 sound like the HD555s.  I have the Berringher 4 port headphone amp, so its very easy to compare all 3 headphones at nearly the same time.  The RS180 sound like the 555s but with no cords!  Also, they seem to weigh the same.  How do they do it?  I used these for 1 day and immediately bought another stand-alone set (you can use 4 headphones with one transmitter).  My wife and I watched the last Downtown Abbey with our matching headphones and it was such a pleasure.  Being able to move around, not get tangled in 20 feet of cable (we used to use the 555 and 518 to watch movies on our home theater projector) and have flawless sound with no static or drop or hum.  So the RS180 sound better than the HD518, as good as the HD555 (my former favorite headphones), and have no wires.  So why not 5 stars (I'd give them 4.5 if I could)?Well, going wireless makes life a little more complicated.  Pairing additional headphones with an existing transmitter was harder than it should have been.  The buttons (as every other review says) are hard to press by feel.  They have a balance (why?), which is easy to hit by mistake instead of volume.  The off button is between the volume up and down, so it's easy to turn them off when you meant to change volume.  What a poor design.I was able to get them to lose the signal by putting my iphone5 right next to the transmitter while downloading an app.  It's hard to do, but I was able to get the signal to drop.  But the iphone has to be within a few inches of the transmitter.My first floor is around 1200 feet, and the headphones work all around the first floor.  But if I go out the slider onto the deck, they start to lose the signal, and it's only 20 feet from the transmitter.  So, it seems to work fine in open space but doesn't handle walls or windows very well.But for using it in the room with the transmitter, and have such awesome sound and no wires, it's absolutely worthwhile to have two sets of these.  I'm glad I got them and wish I got them sooner.  I now use the 518s at work, and my son the movie editor grabbed the 555s.
