VFew Fatal Flaws - Update
p327
sg5
VI've wanted a set of these since forever, and finally due to the price I got a pair.Pros:They are comfortable, have long battery life and look nice.  They are also simple to set up and sound decent.  The range is decent, but certainly not worth bragging about.People mention the button layout on the headset being different, and they are absolutely right, haven't decided whether that is a pro or con yet.Cons:  The sound quality is only marginally better than that of my 5 year old USB Creative Fatality headset which was 1/4 the price of the RS180.The way you turn the RS180 on is very, very counter-intuitive.  You have to push a button on both the headset and transmitter, and the transmitter is so light you have to hold it while pushing the button.  Why they don't have it turn on as soon as it's lifted is beyond me.And the deal breakers.  There is a low volume, high pitch whine coming from the right ear cup.  A quick google search reveals that a few (I could only find 2) other people have the same issue, and ended up replacing the set to fix it, so this is what I will be doing.I also experienced having the audio cut off twice this morning while watching a movie, which is a bit disturbing since the transmitter is about 3ft away from where I was sitting.My general attitude towards the RS180 at this point is that they are not worth the price premium.  There are some very similar items on the market at much lower price points.Once I get my replacement set, I will update my review accordingly, but for now it is -1 star for how you turn them on (yes, it's that inconvenient) and -1 for the whine.--UPDATE 24Jun14--The replacement set has the same whine as the initial set I purchased.  This leads me to believe that it is part of a design flaw and not a fluke.  For a relatively high end set and the number of positive reviews, I would not expect this.  The whine is only in the right ear cup, and occurs when the transmitter and headset are both powered on, the audio cable doesn't need to be attached for this to occur.I use this set with my computer, and after every system sound (click noise from opening folders, etc) there is a short, substantially louder whine.  I should also note that I experience none of this with other (wired) headphones, and that it occurs on the RS180s even with no other wireless device turn on that may have been causing some flavor of interference.
