VThe first thing is to make sure you know what you are getting.  This is a set of wireless headphones meant for use within the home.  The charging base plugs into any sort of audio source just like a normal headphone jack, and the idea is to be able to wander around listening to your audio source with no cords.  They are not sound-cancelling headphones, their primary purpose is to protect your apartment neighbors or others in your home who may not want to hear your electronics at full volume.  Now, on to the review.I bought this product nearly two years ago, and the ratio of cost to how much use/pleasure I get out of this device is one of the best/highest of anything I own, right up there with my phone, PC, and bed.  I use these headphones in my small studio apartment, plugged directly into my main sound system so every device I own can play through these.I don't know how else to say it; they're phenomenal.  I'll try to list some of the highlights:-The sound is crisp and clear, it allows high volume with no loss in quality that I can detect.  I am no audiophile but I do love my music, and these are wonderful.-The comfort on your head is stunning, possibly the best feature of the product.  I can give it the highest possible compliment, which is that I very frequently forget I'm even wearing them and sometimes actually walk out of the apartment in them.  Unbelievable comfort, even when I wear them all day for gaming and music (6-8 hours on a weekend).-Charging is as easy as possible, simply place the headphones on the cradle and off they go.-Battery life is everything you could need.  I've used these for upwards of 12+ hours without needing a charge, I have never had them die on me unless I forget to place them back on the cradle.-Audio is instant, absolutely no delay detectable by the human nervous system (or, I suppose, not detectable by THIS human's nervous system...)I am unable to speak to the range of the headphones, since my apartment is rather small, but I have no problem using them in the kitchen, which is probably 20 feet from the charging base and has a solid wall between.  If you'd like to get more details on distance, I suggest looking to other reviews.  As stated above, these are not sold as sound-cancelling headphones, so you can still hear things around you if they are loud enough, and if there is anyone else in the room with you they will likely hear a faint murmur of what you are listening to, especially at higher volumes.With all that said, I am happy to give this product an 5-star rating with no caveats or qualifications.  If and when this product ceases to function someday, if I am unable to have it fixed I will simply purchase another set.  They're just that good.
