VGreat product and great purchase!!
p560
sg5
VI have waited a long time for wireless headphones that can do what these can do.  I have gone through several cheaper pairs that either weren't comfortable, sounded terrible - and often both.  I was blown away by these headphones after first listen.  I needed a pair of headphones that I could use late at night but wouldn't cripple my movie watching experience.  These things work beautifully, and I am able to keep that quality through every room in my house and even outside.  I've been using them as regular speakers during the day now while working, using my TV as a Pandora/Tune In Radio player and the sound doesn't drop for a second.One note - these are not noise cancelling headphones - if you were these, and there is noise around you, you will here it.  I find it a nice balance, as the soundstage is wide and clear, but if the phone rings I will hear it subtly.  This "open air" design also seems to give the sound a richer, clearer sound - especially during movies.  While nothing can replace a true surround sound experience, these do a great job of giving you that effect.Hooking them up is a breeze - and even though they suggest charging for 16 hours, the batteries (which are marked as pre-charged) worked right out of the box, and the first charge took less than a hour to complete.It's also nice that you can hook into either an analog output (which will allow you to listen directly from any A/V source) or more importantly, if you are using an A/V receiver like mine which cuts the speakers off when you plug in any headphone jack.  Not a problem for me in that I usually want my speakers off, but for someone just looking to "add" the headphones to the entertainment equipment without cutting out the speakers for someone else who might be enjoying the same medium.After about a week, I told my wife that it's one of the most rewarding purchases I have made for our living room.  I highly recommend these!
