VExceeded expectations
p583
sg5
VI read many reviews on these before ordering them.  I use them a lot for watching TV and there was one review I read that concerned me some.  It said if you watch TV with the TV speakers on (for other people to listen) that there was enough of a delay in the sound to the headphones that it would sound out of sync and be annoying.  I have experimented with this and have not found this to be a problem at all.  I have my TV connected to a system with 5.1 surround sound and have noticed that if I turn the TV volume up at the same time you can hear both and while I don't like the mixing, it is not out of sync.  The same is true of the headphones.  I can hear both at the same time but they are in sync, there is not really a delay or an echo.  I also read in another review that there is a lot of sound that leaks out because they are an open design.  That is also an exaggeration.  Yes, some sound does leak out, but at normal listening levels other people in the room wouldn't really hear it. If you were lying next to someone in bed with the TV speakers off and they were trying to sleep they might notice the sound but it would not be enough to wake them if they were already sleeping.  I did try covering the outside of the headphones to make them a closed system to see if it would make a difference.  It reduced the quality of the sound I head through the headphones so I removed the covers.  it was just an experiment, I really don't think it's necessary.The range is excellent.  I also have a pair of Sennheiser RS 140s that are 900 Mhz and these have much better range that those do with no hissing or interference at all.  They just sound terrific.  I highly recommend them.  One other comment that is true is the volume controls on the bottom of the right earpiece are difficult to find and adjust while wearing the headphones.  I solved that problem by putting two drops of glue on the volume + and one drop on the volume - buttons and now I can find them with no trouble at all.  I just used 5 minute epoxy for the job.  They are great, I'm glad I got them.
