VAlmost Perfect!
p696
sg5
VI have been using my Sennheiser RS 180 Digital Wireless Headphone System for five weeks now.  It is by far the best performing wireless headset I've ever used.  I went through three previous brands.  Two of them were such a pain to use I threw them in the trash.  Literally!  The third one stopped working after about 6 months of use.  The Sennheiser RS 180 is a solid performing unit thus far.  It charges simply and easily.  It links up between headset and transmitter base in a instant.  No tuning required as with the analog types.  The sound is excellent in my book.  The highs are crisp, the mid-range/speech areas are clear and the bass sounds are very solid but not booming.  The surround sounds are incredible.  It makes watching movies with outstanding sound tracks a real treat.  I have only two issues with this headset.  The range of operation is not what I thought it should be.  The sound starts breaking up at about 25 feet but because I am sitting maybe 10 feet from my big screen 99% of the time this is not a big deal.  The thing I dislike most is the volume up/on-off/volume down button set on the underside of the right ear piece.  It's difficult to feel them at times.  I often turn the unit off while trying to adjust the volume down.  However this is a quality headset.  It is worth it's high price tag in my opinion.  Everything concidered I would recommend this headset highly to anyone!
