VFinally decent wireless headphones
p773
sg5
VI had some reservations on these after reading some of the reviews saying that they are small or snug, because I have a ginormous head.  My hat size is about 8 1/8, and I'm 6'8 so I'm just a large person in general.  So imagine my surprise when they arrive working as advertised and even very comfortably fitting my head.  The top band that holds the two cups together actually seems to flex quite a bit as I wear them, making for a much more comfortable fit after I'd worn them for a couple of days than when they were first out of the box.  All the parts that touch your head are soft and velvety.  After breaking them in for a couple of days, they fit my head like a large comfortable head glove.  I've worn them already for hours on end with very little ear fatigue.My house is kind of small, but it's on two levels and there is nowhere I go in my house that I don't receive a clear signal.  Sound is very good and bass response is quite acceptable for this type of open headphone.  Whenever I've detected minor static or distortion, it has always ended up being in the source not in the headphones (I need to get some higher bitrate MP3s).  The only minor negatives I've noted is that there is a brief <1 second drop in the signal about every hour or so, the fact that you have to get up and push a button on the transmitter to turn it on (I am not too lazy to manage that), and the button placement.  Buttons are functional and with some practice I should be able to distinguish what's what without looking.  Protip from the manual:  If you accidentally hit one of the balance buttons, you can hold down both balance buttons at the same time to reset.  Oh, and one other potential drawback:  they make the wearer look like a total dork.  But it's totally worth it.
