VGood headphones, frustrating control system
p838
sg5
VThe good: these headphones sound good, are of quality workmanship, and fit comfortably.The bad: the control system will make you want to cry. I use these headphones at the office so that I can listen to music while working. The problem is that every time I leave my desk to attend a meeting or get something from the printer, my impulse is to put the headphones back on the transmitter base/charger to ensure that the batteries stay charged. This powers down the headphones, which is ok. What's not ok is that it also powers off the base transmitter and breaks the pairing between transmitter and headphones. This means that when I come back, I not only have to turn on the headphones I also have to turn on the transmitter and wait for the pairing process to complete before I get any audio. This is ridiculous. The headphones obviously transmit commands back to the transmitter for the pairing to take place so why doesn't the transmitter turn on when I turn the headphones on? Why don't the headphones and transmitter stay paired until I say otherwise? I feel especially bad for people who use these headphones at home where the transmitter is across the room from the listening location. Let's take this one step farther and ask why taking the headphones off the charger doesn't automatically turn the system on so that the phones are working by the time they're on your head? All I wanted is the functionality of wired headphones without the problems of getting tangled up in or damaging the cord and this headphone system falls short.
