VGreat headphones with a couple caveats
p975
sg5
VPros:-Excellent range with no connection issues whatsoever.-Sound great for being wireless-The battery has never ever died on me, and I have occasionally fallen asleep with these still going. 8+ hours later, they are always still going strong.Cons:-The construction materials could be better. The plastic around the drivers seems pretty cheap. It didn't take them very long to start creaking.-On occasion, I hear rattling in the right cup that I can't seem to get rid of. It makes this noise during playback, so it is very annoying. Probably related to the issue of cheap construction materials. **edit haven't heard rattle in a long time. See below,**Overall I am still very happy with these. The creaking is only an issue when they are in my hands, so it isn't really a big deal. I said the construction materials seemed cheap because they creak and make noises, but they have lasted me this long without breaking. That is saying a lot considering I have woken up half of a dozen times with these under me (they creaked well before that).**Edit Sep 2015**Well, they are still going strong. I have to hand it to Sennheiser, these are some excellent headphones. While my headphones have continued to slowly come apart (no thanks to the way I treat them), They still sound fantastic. No issues with battery life, they are still mostly holding together, and the rattle is completely gone somehow! I think the culprit may have been a broken clip on the pad plate. One of them is missing now and I haven't heard the rattle for a long time.I'm going to eventually pick up a new pair of headphones for these, especially now that I heard that I can use multiple pairs with a single transmitter. I would give these 4.5 stars if Amazon allowed it.
