VExcellent Sound Quality
p1098
sg5
VOverall, I've been really happy with this purchase.First, it was really easy to set up the headphone system. I'm only moderately technically inclined, but it only took me perhaps five minutes to set everything up.Second, although I'm not an audiophile, I've been very impressed with the quality of the sound on these headphones; I particularly like the audio-leveling feature. That said, contrary to how these headphones are described on Amazon, these headphones DON'T have "dynamic surround sound."  I wish they did and I wonder why they don't, as the lower-level Model RS 170 headphones have surround sound.Third, I've generally been satisfied with the range of these headphones. I live in a 2 story, 2900 square-foot house, and I typically get reception just about anywhere in the house. I do periodically get a brief "hiccup" in the sound when I'm in the remote areas of the house, when I'm outside grilling on the patio, and when I walk into the garage. None of those distances exceed 150 feet, so I do question whether these headphones truly have a 320-foot line-of-sight range range that Sennheiser advertises. But, again, the range is generally fine for my purposes.Fourth, the headphones are really comfortable, and in my opinion, the headphones and base look handsome and cool.  However, the headphones and base don't seem to be constructed with particularly high-quality materials. The plastic feels light and thin -- which could be a positive, but makes me wonder whether they could break easily. (Mind you, they HAVEN'T broken, but I don't have high confidence that they could withstand much punishment.)Fifth, the volume and balance controls on the headphones are a bit cumbersome to operate. The volume and balance are controlled by small, low-profile buttons on the outside of the right ear cup. For me, it's been tough to find and operate those buttons by feel. So, to adjust the volume or balance, I've typically needed to remove the headphones to find and work the buttons. That can become a bit annoying after a while.
