VSeinnheiser Wireless Headphones
p1110
sg5
VI have owned many wireless headphones. I am not an electronic geek but have all the geek equipment. In the final analysis the most important thing is how do they sound to you, comfort, and ability to deliver what you want.  These have clearly been the best wireless phones I have ever owned. I had been using the Seinnheiser RS-160. My complaint about them was they were heavy and not very comfortable. More importantly the controls on the earphones are elevated. If you are in bed watching TV or doing something else you can very easily change the volume by rolling over on the side of the phone where the controls are located. I seemed to do this several times each time I used them.The new phones are light and extremely comfortable. They sync with the transmitter quickly and you have a light on both the earphones and transmitter that lets you know they are synced. The ear phones have recessed controls for volume,balance,sync,etc. They are small so you may need to take them off to make adjustments until you use them for a while. The transmitter can be placed behind doors or anywhere and they will still perform. The phones automatically charge on the transmitter. I really do not know how you would make a better earphone set than these but since there are some that cost $500 I guess you can. These have been great and I have had them for about 7 months. I have no idea how long the batteries will last and I have used them for up to 4 hours continuously with no loss of sound. They are not inexpensive but quality is not cheap. Like most things some people will not like these and some will think they are the greatest thing since sliced bread. Good luck. Of course with Amazon you can always send them back. Does not get better than that.
