sg5
VAnother great product from Sennheiser.  The sound is excellant and as someone said in another post when using these headphones this is the first time I hear all of the words in a movie or TV show.  The sound is crystal clear and presents a surround sound type of image.  Price is high but then again high quality head phone that are not wireless aren't a whole lot less expensive.I agree with the majority of reviewers that the buttons on the headphones are not easily accessed (especially the volume controls).  However, having said that in reality once I set the volume I haven't thouched it since so it becomes a moot point.  IF I want the volume changed I use my remove to increase/decrease the volume on the source which solves the problem.Wireless range was satisfactory.  This spec is highly dependant on your individual room/house makeup.  Specs like these are always made in open areas so as to standardize this measurement.  I'm able to go to several different rooms and not lose the signal.Depending on your environment you will either like or dislike the "Open-Aire" noise suppression or lack thereof.  In my case I don't have external noise sources as that would be a real problem as you can hear quite a bit of outside noise/sound when using these headphones.  Open-Aire is good in that when someone comes into the room and asks you a question you can easily hear the question without taking off the headphones.  However, if a constant noise/sound source were present this would be a problem.Headphone fatigue is always a problem when wearing headphones for extended periods of time (like a full length movie).  The Sennheiser phones are the most comfortable that I have worn to date.  I can easily watch a full length movie without the typical ear pain that most headphones give you.  Also they are light enough that there are no other pressure points that become a problem after a certain length of time.Setting up the system was a snap and basically a plug and play process.  For me this has solved the problem of wanting higher volumes when I watch TV, movies, etc. whereas my wife likes the opposite.  Now we are both happy.  The real negative of this system though is now I rarely use my big surround system that I spent so much money on so it sits there gathering dust:):)
