sg5
VI needed to replace cheaper headphones that had literally fallen apart.  I purchased the Sennheiser RS 180 Digital Wireless Headphone after carefully reviewing their specifications and customer reviews.  I use my headphones for TV viewing. The sturdiest set I found had metal head bands but were bluetooth which I couldn't use.  These have plastic bands (I don't think there is a metal ribbon inside) but appear sufficient if used with care. However, I did notice the set with metal bands were a bit heavy and could become uncomfortable after a while.  The RS 180 is very comfortable due to the light weight, soft velour ear pads, the over the ear design and padding on the head band.  I have some loss of hearing and have a hearing aid (BTE) on one ear. It does not interfere at all with the close fit of the headphones.  The sound is very good.  I turn the TV on, pick up the headphones and press the "ON" button on the stand, press the "ON" button on the headphones and hold them at the stand for a second to sync. I chose these headphones which have the "open" ear design so I could hear other sounds too, i.e. someone addressing you. While being worn the headphones sound adjusting buttons are too smooth to differentiate.  However, it only takes a few seconds to remove the headphones and adjust. Some reviewers have their own cures for this. Since the wireless signal travels through walls, I can hear as I walk through the house. I can turn a second TV on with the same program in another room and listen from the first TV (where the headphones base is connected). I have found these headphones to be enjoyable and hope they stay that way.
