VOutstanding on all fronts
p1211
sg5
V6 months later - updateJust wanted to leave a quick update now that I have owned these for 6 months. I would guess I spend at least half my waking hours wearing these and simply put, they are perfect. They are so light and comfortable that you never get sore ears and quickly forget you even have them on. The sound quality is fantastic and with a little equalizer tweaking on your mp3 or movie software you can really get these sounding just the way you want. One reason I love these, which may affect you, is that they are *not* sound blocking. I need to be able to hear surrounding noise (children) or phones ringing. If you want to block sounds then these are not for you.The wear on these has been great. After about 3 months they definitely adjusted. At first I was afraid that they were losing their structural integrity but this has not been the case. They are as sturdy as ever and seem to have just gone through a breaking in period where they are less stiff and feel even more comfortable to wear. The cordless comfort and freedom is just a bonus. There is zero sound quality loss from the cordless style.About the only complaint I would have, which is user error, is charging. If you wear them all day and then charge them all night you will have a perfect schedule. However these seem to charge in almost real time. Meaning if you wear them all day they literally take all night to charge. Because of this, if you forget a charge they can go dead the next day with no real warning and you can't just pop them on the charger for a quick refill to get you by.I have owned many high end headphones and now own several Sennheiser headphones for travel and home and these are simply as good as it gets. I would never wear anything else unless I were traveling.-------------------Takes some pretty fancy technology to really impress me these days, and but these headphones are nothing but perfection. I have used high end corded headphones for a long time, and have always preferred Sennheiser. After shopping around for a new pair I finally decided to give the wireless a try. I really did not want to waste a bunch of money for a lesser model so I went all in with the RS 180's and I am truely amazed. Not only do they sound better than my old HD595 pair, the wireless mode is truely the next step in multimedia enjoyment. With a fairly simple set up between my iTunes, Apple TV and an iPod remote I can put the headset on and have perfect high end sound quality at my computer for gaming, then walk away with music playing and then go lounge in bed and watch a streaming movie.Provided you remember to charge them every night, you will never run out of battery life. They are extremely comfortable. More so than my previous HD595. The fit is snug on an average size head, and with the over-the-ear style of these, they have no pressure at all on your ears. They are very well cushioned on your head and the material is very high quality and soft, but durable - it also seems quite resistant to debris and can be easily wiped if neccessary though I have not found them to attract much dust at all.They look great. They are a sleek charcoal/black and the charging cradle looks very cool and saves a little bit of desk space instead of having to lay down a giant pair of headphones like I used to. So far I have gone a few rooms nearby. I can't say the true distance as don't have a need to go that far with them, but within a room or two away I have noticed zero quality loss and zero distortion or buzzing or anything of the sort. They are just crystal clear all the time.I have watched action movies, played the latest CoD Black Ops and many other games and listen to a wide variety of music and have really found no weak spot as far as sound depth. They exceed any wired headphones I have used for any of the same activities.If I had one tiny complaint, and this may be true for all wireless headsets of which this is my first - when you are ready to put on the headset and you take it off the cradle to place on your head, you need to click a little button on the cradle and then a button the headset to "find it" and sync them together. Now this takes all of 2 seconds to do but it is an extra step I find just a tad annoying. Generally this just makes me not return them to the cradle until I am done using them for the day and I still usually just set them down on the top of my desk so as not to lose the connection and have to redo it if I place them on the cradle for more than a few minutes. But again, this is a tiny thing and in no way is a criticism of the actual performance of these great phones.
