p1217
sg5
VI got these for my pops to replace his HD555 wired cans that i got him a year earlier, both to watch TV at night.  even before that years ago i got him some Recoton 900 mhz wireless ones but they were hurting his ears.  he liked HD555 for comfort and excellent speech intelligibility but obviously wasn't thrilled about the fact that they were wired.well this headphone solves the problem.  it has all the comfort and sound quality that you would expect from sennheiser and it comes in a wireless package that has a decent range and for the most part doesn't drop the signal, doesn't interfere with wifi or microwave and otherwise just plain works.  the charging stand / base is excellent as well.my father's only gripe with this unit is the volume buttons on the headphone are hard to use in the sense that you can't see them while the headphone is on your head and they are difficult to locate by touch alone.  all the buttons are more or less same shape and next to each other which is obviously a bad design - they should be spaced out and shaped differently to be more usable.but that is a minor gripe, not enough to take off a star of otherwise excellent product.i am a serious audiophile and a speaker builder and while i would never use wireless headphones for music myself i have tested their sound quality with music and it is quite good.  they have more bass and warmer sound than many sennheiser open back cans, but of course nowhere close to my IE8 sennheisers.  rock music sounds very good on these headphones - very balanced.  for electronic music you would probably want something more bass heavy like IE8 which admittedly are not wireless.build quality is simply top notch both on the headphone itself and the base.  while it is all plastic the quality is excellent.  it feels much more solid than you would expect from its light weight.even with the high price i have absolutely no reservations about recommending these for watching TV at night.  they deliver.
