VI love these headphones.  I have been a fan of Sennheiser for years and have pitied people who shell out as much as $ 400 for Beats.  Germans are obsessive, which is why they are such incredible engineers and they did everything right with these. They are lightweight, I have never run out of battery life (of course, I put them back on the stand when I am done with them) and are probably the most comfortable headphones I have ever owned, but the biggest reason I love them is the SOUND.  What I am looking for in a pair of headphones is faithful reproduction of sound, not artificial booming bass, but balanced sound through the range.  The trebles are crisp and clear, the mids and bass are both precise. When I first received them, I listened to a range of music (including the two "standards" I use to sample speakers and headphones, "Abbey Road" by the Beatles, "Aja" by Steely Dan and "Beethoven's 9th Symphony" conducted by Herbert van Karajan and the Berlin Symphony Orchestra on Deutsche Grammaphon.  All were impeccable.  I have also been using them to listen to Blu-ray discs and they are fantastic for that.  I have a 5.1 surround sound system, which I love, but there are times when I want to watch a movie and not disturb others.  When I was shopping, I seriously considered getting the RS 160s, which have a surround sound mode, but I have no complaints about these.  I can walk around the house with them, I listen to music when I cook. I am very glad that I bought them and would highly recommend them to anyone.
