sg5
VI bought this pair of headphones after my old pair (also Sennheisers) were getting old and I got tired of the wires. This pair was on sale at Amazon, so I picked it up. It's pretty simple to use and setup. The instructions/unit are relatively clear and laid out.The sound quality is good and there is no noticeable latency. While I am a gamer and do listen to music, I'm not an audiophile, so your mileage may vary, depending on how stringent your requirements are.Two serious defects in this product are its lack of QC and range. As many others here have noted, my first pair have had a buzzing/static sound (right ear). On the replacement unit, this problem has disappeared, so you should only buy this if you are willing to go through Amazon's (quick and easy) return/replacement system.The second problem is the range. This product will NOT go through more than one or two very thin doors/walls, and will most likely NOT get the promised/advertised range unless you are in a clear open field, so if this is important to you (you like to roam around in a large house, etc.), then this product is NOT for you.
