VExcellent sound for a wireless headphone
p1311
sg5
VI am pleasantly surprised by the sound put out by these wireless cans. I have the RS140 but this takes it up another level. The RS180s are lighter than the RS140s and wearing them for a few hours was very comfortable, sometimes you even forget you are wearing them. The only niggle is your ears do get a little warm after wearing, as compared to the RS140.I compared the performance of the RS170 and RS180 before getting these, and I would recommend you pay a little more for the better sound. If you use the RS170 with bass boost, you get more bass then the RS180. But if you use without bass boost, the sound is really lacking bass and sounds flat compared to the RS180. The RS180 has a bigger soundstage, probably helped by the open air design. I am a long time Sennheiser user and from experience I am not a big fan of leatherette earcups, I find they disintegrate after 1-2 years and get flaky. Go for the velour cushions. I had my RS140 for 4.5 years and I use they almost daily, and to-date the velour cushions are still holding up.
