VWorth the Extra $$$'s
p1377
sg5
VThe sound from these headphones is second to none.  And the nicest thing is that the headphones DO NOT, repeat DO NOT go off and make a horrible white noise sound when the source goes to silence for any length of time (like the RS 120's do).  You can set them down for a long time and when you come back, beautiful SILENCE until you turn the music back on - then it's total immersion in the sound.  It takes a while to learn the push-button volume & balance controls, but after a while you will know where the on/off switch is and other controls.  The ear cups are comfortable and I forget that I'm listening to headphones after a few minutes.  The transmitter can project a pretty good distance through walls and structures, but I wouldn't push it too far.  I find that I can walk out to the curb before the signal starts to break up.  I agonised over the cost of these 'phones, but now that I've used them for some time, I have totally forgotten the price.  They are worth every penny.
