VFantasticalent
p1383
sg5
VThese digital wireless headphones don't have background hiss and white noise, so my years of searching are over! I don't like noise, and these headphones don't add any. It has a good range too. When the sound drops out from being too far away, it sounds like a brief, faint chirp (not a slap to the head). I was surprised it works as well as it does with such a lightweight switchmode 5V power supply. I might eventually replace the stock power supply with hefty shielded linear 5V supply, just to see if it can get even better. The no-modification trick to feeling the volume buttons is to use your ring finger or pinky (more sensitive) to find the gap between Vol- and the Balance button. Vol+ is easier to find. Synchronizing the headphones to the transmitter seemed a bit iffy, but not a problem with some sound playing into the transmitter. I used a separate charger to charge the AAAs faster, before twisting the earmuffs unlocked to put them in the battery compartments.
