VTransmitter Auto-off feature a nuisance
p1401
sg5
VMy 82 year-old father has been using the RS140 headphones for a few years and liked them. We decided to give him a new RS180 set for Christmas. The sound quality on both is really good, but the new RS 180 set is not as user friendly. To begin with, the controls on the headset are more difficult for him to operate as his hands and fingers are large and he is losing his dexterity. However, the biggest problem is that the new set's transmitter has an auto-off function if the headphones are turned off for five minutes. I believe this is an energy saving feature, but there is no option to disable it or extend the auto-off time. Because my father's mobility is very limited, it is a huge inconvenience for him to have to get up from his chair and make it across the room to turn the transmitter back on. I have provided this feedback to Sennheiser and suggested that they include a disable option and/or options for longer times for the auto-off to trigger.
