p1527
sg5
VThe sound  and physical feel is between open air and closed earphones:  the sound is not as live and transparent sounding as wired Sennheiser or Grado open air phones, but, it is not as boxy as closed phones often are. Bass is elevated and lower midrange is slightly recessed.The sound is very clean and interference free, the range indoors is excellent. The phones are comfortable, not light but not too heavy, and they are secure on the head while walking or in other non-athletic indoor activities, much more stable than the RS120. The on-off, volume and balance controls on the earphone are a bad design. They are small push buttons that blend into the surrounding plastic surface and are hard to tell apart.  The RS 120 is much better in this respect.
