VVery Good Headphone
p1951
sg5
VFirst, let me tell you, if you need some information before buying these headphones you can discard the 1 and 2 stars reviews right off the bat.  They are from two kinds of people for the most part.  One would post a review before even trying the item, like r William ward who wrote \u201cHaven't figured out how to install it\u201d yet.  The other, received a defective unit and is pissed, like Robert E. Kirk who chimed \u201cThe Sennheiser RS 180 Wireless Headphones sounded great for one time, after that I could not get them to connect to the base.\u201d  Once you passed this crowd you might be able to read some meaningful reviews.For my part I am satisfied with these headphones.  I use them for TV and music and they have comported themselves well on both counts.  The major drawback with them is the design of the volume and balance control.  What was the engineer thinking?  I compared them to only one other headphone, the V-Moda Crossfade M-80 which I like because of their size and comfort.  The Sennheiser is better in terms of frequency response as they seem to reach the entire spectrum.  They seem to keep going in the higher frequency region where the V-Moda had stopped.  I compared them mostly to my Hi-Fi system and they seem to hold their ground pretty well.  They are not as complete but I didn't expect them to be.  I have two 12-inch Martin Logan subs and my room is acoustically treated so I can for instance adjust the bass to my liking whereas with the phones I don\u2019t have that luxury.  The bass is nevertheless adequate.  Sound stage and imaging is what it is with headphones and I don\u2019t think they can be changed.  The center stage is always going to be on top of your head instead of in front of you.  Apart from that, they are very competent.  I have them connected to the stereo output of my venerable Sony C555ES and couldn't hear any difference when I introduce a headphone amplifier (FiiO E11) in the path, so I am using them without the amp that does make a noticeable difference with the V-Moda.  I am very happy that I can move around the house and be able to take the music with me.  I doubt any reasonable person would regret buying them.
