VLove them!  Work flawlessly and perfect for our needs.
p1957
sg5
VThe RS 180 is the first large headphone I have ever purchased.  So, nothing to compare them to.  But, they actually provide a more enjoyable tv listening experience than my high dollar surround system.  Wife is early to bed type and I work a crazy half days, half nights shift work schedule.  We needed something to allow tv watching without waking one another.  For our particular single listener situation they have performed flawlessly.  If you need a simultaneous set-up for someone who is hard of hearing, these are open ear cup and will probably give the slight echo effect that other reviewers have noted.  Purchase accordingly and get a closed cup design if that is what you need.  Also, these may not be the best for in bed since sound does leak from the open cup design.Our reciever allowed for either optical or standard output so, no issues there as some with optical only have noted.  Set-up was extremely simple, standard base input cord to the back of the receiver, power cord to strip or outlet, then nothing more than plugging to receiver headphone jack when using and unplugging when done.  The sound is wonderful and volume more than enough for anyone with normal hearing.  We can move freely around the house and have never had any dropouts with 100 ft probably the max distance we ever get from the base.  They are quite comfortable and not overly hot to wear for extended periods even though a large headset.  Also, we have never experienced the slightest buzz, hum or feedback problem while using these.The only slight issue with these is the volume and balance controls not being easy to distinguish from one another.  We have found this to be a minor inconvenience compared to the quality in every other respect.  As other reviewers have noted, you can simply put a drop of glue or, glue a small bead on a couple of the buttons to help with this if you don't want to or can't remember the configuration.  Simply put, if your needs and intended use are the same as ours, you cannot go wrong with these headphones.  If you have any problems, all I can say is you must have received a subpar set.  We could not be more satisfied with ours.
