VGood but one minor annoyance.
p1969
sg5
VI purchased these after my Sennheiser RS130 wireless headphones finally died after 5 years of constant use. And if I were basing the review entirely on sound quality alone these would get 5 stars. The sound quality is fantastic, instruments can be heard very clearly in music, for movies it makes the sound effects sound more realistic and the dialogue more clear, and they work well for gaming, though they are not ideal for games due to the lack of simulated surround sound, which is something that the RS130's did very well.The build quality is also quite nice. I normally hate glossy plastic but the plastic on these is pretty nice. The headband feels pretty sturdy and the earpads/headband pads are all replaceable. However the first few days of use gave me massive headaches due to how tight these headphones were squeezing my head. However I have a very large head, I wear a size 8 in fitted hats so this probably won't be an issue for most people. They have become more comfortable each day as they get stretched out.However not everything is perfect. I discovered very quickly that these headphones will sometimes change frequencies all of a sudden and kill my wireless network. Its not a constant problem either, sometimes I will go a few days without this happening, other times it will kill my wireless to the point where I have to reset everything. I tried the suggestion the Sennheiser tech support gave me but it only fixed the problem for about 36 hours. It could just be a compatibility with my specific router. I have considered returning these because of this but so far the annoyance is minor enough to keep them. I would hate having to go back to wired headphones as I have a tendency to break wired headphones very quickly.Don't let this wireless issue dissuade you from getting these though. It seems that most people who bought these do NOT have any issues with interference at all. And I have to say, Sennheiser's tech support responded very quickly to my email and was very eager to try to help.
