VIve used Amazon for well over 10 years, bought tons of stuff, but never wrote a review.I just had to write a review for these puppies.Quick Review: AWESOME! Just BUY THEM! well worth the price! They just work, and they work AWESOME!They just came in the mail today, and i quickly plugged them in, and put them on the charger... The instructions say to charge them for 16 hours. I couldnt wait.. after an hour on the charger, i had to hear how they sound.AWESOME!I listen to music while I work on the computer, a lot of electronica, so you know how that can bug some people. especially hearing the bump bump bump at 3am. And you need to listen to electronica on the loud side. It keeps the heart rate up, and keeps ya in the zone.  If you are a "vampire coder" like i am, you know what im talking about.Very light weight. Yea..they feel a bit cheap, but hey, they need to make them light, and plastic is pretty darn light, and economical. They are already pretty darn expensive. So I can understand their choice in materials. I dont think they were meant to be used while paint balling, or while you spar MMA style. And they were not meant for your 8 year old overly hyper active, A.D.D. kid.Distance. I have the base transmitter about 3 feet from my head. Its next to my computer. Tons of cables, octopus power outlets and wireless crap nearby.. no troubles. Perfect sound, and apparently my wifi still works.  I walked out to the back yard, and it was perfect sound.I just did a test..it doesnt like SCREEN DOORS.. screen doors, how they are fabricated will kill the signal. Screens are used to control Wifi signals too (google it). So if you are getting some cut out, then look around for screens. Its probably blocking the signal.But going through the garage, i made it 1/2 way down my drive way. 2000 Sq Foot house, built 2000, So Cali. to give you a rough idea.The transmitter is located in the office on the back side of the house.I dont know what that KlearSound technology they use is, but it seems like its transmitting digital signals to the head set, and the head set is decoding and playing them back. So you dont get any fuzzy buzz sounds like those other cheap wireless headsets.. You might get cut out, but no fuzzy. And i think they buffer it too. Sorta like the skip buffer used in Car CD players. But thats just a guess. The quality sure sounds like its doing something like that.Ok..something that immediately caught my attention.. was the ear muff material. Its like a velvety feel. and WARM. If you are a girl who is always cold (arent all girls always cold?) then you will love em.. Im HOT BLOODED (check it and see) , and they feel warm on my head, not hot, but warm. I took a quick search on the net to see if they have that other material (cold plasticy feeling) as a replacement..didnt see em..i will keep looking..And the infamous BUTTONS.. if you read reviews on these guys, everyone crys about the buttons..Yes..i have to agree, they should have put more time in the button design and placement.But if you practice a bit.. you can feel the Volume Up..its big and angled.rub your finger down and you feel the raised plastic of the POWER button.Well the next button is VOLUME down..then you get a flat "spacer", and the next two are Left/Right balance.Although not perfect, quite usable without taking the headsets off. But heck.. i dont do hard labor, so my finger tips are not callused. :)And remember you can still control the volume from your audio source (Computer, Receiver, TV, etc) using its own remote. So no biggy for me.The "Open design".. its odd, you can still sorta hear the outside world. Like right now, i can hear my puppies barking in the back yard. but just barely.If the purpose of the headsets was to COMPLETELY drown out your crying baby, you might want to look at a closed design one. Or duct tape the vents.If you just came back from Best Buy, returning those PIECE of SH***EET Sony 900Mhtz wireless headphones, and wondering if there was anything decent out there, you found em! the rs180's!!!! And they are not just decent..they are AWESOME!If you are STILL on the fence after reading all these awesome reviews, just remember you can return them if they dont meet your majestic standards.Amazons Customer Service has always been Triple A+++ in my experience.The search is over Indiana Jones... you FOUND IT!Ok..need to get back to work..the wife isnt going to be too happy knowing that we are $224 dollars short on the mortgage. j/k :)
