VSolid product
p2005
sg5
VIt could have been other reviews that had me overly anticipate the wave of goodness that I'll hear when I put these headphones on. So I guess I can't say my first impressions were that great.I just didn't find the sound quality THAT great. I'm not saying they're bad, but blow my mind? Wasn't sure. (Note: I've never tried any other wireless headphones before, so nothing to really judge against, sound is purely comparison between other earbuds I've listened to)I noticed a high pitched buzz in the background, not good, so I was wondering what the heck it was. Well after some digging, turns out that the input for the headphones are best if there's more power supplied, so my TV was pushed to 80% of the volume, background noise (because the Auto leveling didn't have to kick in) was gone.And of course then there was the source of the track I'm listening to as well. Youtube and downloaded videos well, just don't really cut it. I put in some lossless classical sound track... okay NOW I'm blown away. Cello pieces were amazingly clear, to the point where I can make out the musicians' slap on the 'fret board' (okay dunno what its called on a Cello) during more dramatic bars. Fantastic.I don't know if these headphones require burn in periods as some earbuds do. I hope they do though, because I'm just liking them more and more.Build quality, I like the lightness of the product, the plastic bits, don't scream 'high quality' but they're not bad. The felt ear cushions feel nice against the skin, don't over heat too bad, and I'm someone who is sensitive to heat.Range, personally within my 2000sqft house, I've had a few places that cut off (my room is top floor corner). Far ends of the house I get cut off, but thats through walls and floors... not bad at all.Overall, I'm really liking these headphones. Price wise, if you get them at a decent price, its totally worth it, I'm not sure MSRP, but that's me.Surprises to me, were that these were open headphones, so noise isolation is not its strong point. Having never had a headphone before (only earbuds) it'll take some adjusting for the weird hair I end up having after long periods of wearing them.
