VAlmost perfect
p2065
sg5
VPros: Awesome sound (usually), very comfortable, very good battery life, good range, can use standard batteriesCons: Long charging time, charger is a little flakyI've these for just over two years now, and they are pretty much awesome. The sound quality is excellent (particularly with music),the batteries last from 6-10 hours (depending on volume) and they are extremely comfortable - possibly the most comfortable headphones I've ever used. The range is also quite good; I've walked from my second floor apartment to my car in the parking lot with no dropouts.The primary reason that I gave 4 instead of 5 stars has to do with charging. While the batteries last quite a while, recharging takes forever (according to Sennheiser's site, it takes 16 hours from zero to fully charged). This seems excessive, considering that there are only two AAA batteries. The other charging problem has to do with the base itself.The base seems to be very particular about placement. When placing the headphones on the charger, it seems as though they should just slot in and begin charging; unfortunately, this is not always the case. It is very easy to place the headphones on the base, get the charging light, and then any movement stops the charging. The headphones need to be placed just right. There is also no warning that the batteries are about to die; they simply shut off.Overall, these are very good headphones. The sound quality is great, they are incredibly comfortable, and the charging problems can be defeated by having some AAA batteries arround.
