VActually, this is my second set of Sennheiser headphones. I owned a pair for several years now, for my living room TV. My wife only recently tried them on, and I had to get an extra pair for her, despite an important shortcoming. The buttons, are almost impossible to access without removing the headphones and turning the light on in the room.- They are too small, with no space between them. Your tactile senses are futile.- They are the same color as the body of the unit, making them impossible to see in low light conditions.- The balance buttons have proven to be useless after several years of use. They actually add another annoying factor: if you push one of them by mistake while trying to adjust the volume, you're bound to miss a good part of the movie you're watching. You have to turn on the lights, take them off and put them back on several times while you try to find the correct balance setting through trial-and-error. It really sucks!I took off two stars for this. I'll give it five stars when the manufacturer removes the stupid balance buttons, places the volume and power buttons at a reasonable distance from each other, and makes them white or a another bright color, DIFFERENT from the rest of the device, so they can be distinguished in the dark.On the bright side, the headphones reach every corner of my 1,200sf home without static or drops, and the sound quality is great! Kudos for using standard-sized rechargeable batteries, and reasonably easy to replace when the time comes.
