VYears back my brother and I picked up some Sennheiser wired around the ear headphones for some home studio work and when I started to look for a good set of wireless those memories brought me to Sennheiser.I bought these to use with music and home theater for when the kids are in bed and the wife does not want to be disturbed.  My main system is a 7.1 with a mix of CerwinVega, Klipsch, Infinity and Advent speakers.  Even my 'normal' pc speakers are Infinity.I tried the RS120s and was dissappointed. The static bump between tracks and when automatically shutting down was unacceptable, even if the sound was acceptable. Plus the on-ear feature was not something I could endure for several hours.When these arrived I was impressed. The sound is good.  When not in use - end of album, film, etc they are silent.  They have just enough pressure to stay on the head without being uncomfortable.A feature not highlighted is these use removable standard AA rechargeable batteries. So if you find that you ran them dry (because you did not set them back on the charger over night) you can swap them out with a fresh pair. I also like this for longevity.  My last pair of cheapies had non-replaceable cells and after a year would start to alert the battery was low after only an hour - then proceed to chirp and work for nearly to more hours - talk about ruing the experience.  (Thanks GE.)I even went for the Amazon Wherehouse deal and had no problems - save a few dollars.
