VThese sound great if you plan on simply sitting in a chair or walking around a quiet house. The open back design makes them less desirable in noisier environments. If you plan on trying to use them with your musical instrument, don't bother. There is about a 1/4 of a second delay which makes playing the guitar frustrating. I was hoping to use them at home late at night. I know they were not intended for that purpose, but it is a little irritating that you can connect up to 4 headsets. Seems like that would be a great option. The open back design does allow you to easily here your amplifier if you want to play over a music track. I do that with the drums quite a bit and it works really well.They sound really good and the range is great if you don't have too many walls in the way. I have two sets of headphones that each have independent volumes. They are just loud enough to wipe out most moderate background noise. Battery life is not bad and they are super easy to recharge. The design is cool and they are well made. These are defiantly for the audiophile on a budget, headphones can get REALLY expensive. These sound way better than a lot of more expensive corded headphones I own. If you listen to Rap or music with heavy bass, these might not fit your taste. If you are a musician you will want to check out wireless monitors.
