VSurprisingly good sound
p2172
sg5
VThese headphones boast exceptional clarity especially for a wireless set.  I have had some very bad wireless sets before - Sennheisers included.  I have the Sennheiser (wired) HD598s and usually have to eq the treble up to help distinguish dialogue.  I do have some hearing loss in the higher frequencies so I was surprised I could understand the dialogue much easier (no eq) with the RS 180s.  I am not sure what that means in the audiophile world (given my hearing loss) but I like them since they do what I am looking for.  The RS 180s have a nice open sound stage and provide solid bass response (slightly more bass response than the 598s but still very tight) making music listening and movie watching enjoyable as well.  They also have noise leveling so the loud passages do not further my hearing loss.  They only get 4 stars because I hate the adjustment buttons.  They should have spread the controls out - perhaps even putting balance controls on the other phone.  I am always hitting the wrong buttons.  Also, these phones are not as comfortable as my HD598s - a little more clamping pressure than I like.PS:  And neither the RS180 or the HD598 play Celine Dion like my old HD540s did!
