VIts been about 24 hours since I received my Sennheiser 180. FIrst impression is that it looked cheap. Its all plastic which is fine if the plastic was durable but this plastic seems like a good drop would crack them. I feel like I just bought these from a dollar store because thats how the plastic feels like.I am nervous that my kids or wife will break them.After getting over the plastic that makes up all of the 180 the sound is really impressive. I live in a high wifi area and I get no distorted sound. I did buy a couple of wireless headphones before and I heard nothing but click or distorted noise so I am happy with this alone. I also walked all over the house and the volume stayed the same and that is really impressive. They feel comfortable and very light. Only problem is that the headphones can be heard by others. So I wouldnt buy these for plane trips because everyone around you will hear what you are hearing.Overall I think they are charging you too much for what you are getting.I am happy with them but if they break because my kids drop them or they fall off my desk that 230 I spent on them will leave me feeling very unhappy.
