VI spent two weeks deciding on a new head phone and finally decided on this.My biggest concern is the quality and the potential for interference.I wanted to buy RS 220, but decided against after hearing bad review on interferrence.On the RS 180, interferrence occurs occasionally, but is tolerable in general. Interferrence is worse when I walk next to the micro wave (obviously) or if I am in intense gaming over the wifi, but usually it is not too bad.Quality wise, at first I thought the head phone is aweful because the sound would fade in and out slowly and constantly. (as in becoming loud slightly for a while then becoming quiet slightly, in a periodic fashion). This went away after I bought a DAC to the headphone to. I am surprised that with such an expensive headphone it didn't come with it's own DAC and you needed to actually go but an external one. I got the sound blaster x-fi 5.1 for around 55$.the bottom line is, if you have a good receiver, this head phone works. sounds better than my wired low-end image s4, but does not sound so good that would blow me away.
