VRS180 worth the upgrade from the RS120
p2231
sg5
VUpgrading from my Sennheiser RS120s. Great to watch TV at night when everyone else goes to bed. My old RS120 was great but a little annoying having to tune the frequency in at times and it would get static if you turned your head wrong.  The RS180 has excellent sound quality when the volume to the TV is set to 0. Because of the slight time delay due to signal processing the sound of a faint dog barking like sound can be heard when the TV sound is able to be heard along with the head phone sound.  To Sennheiser's credit this is noted on their website.  One thing I liked about the RS120 was that you did not have to turn the power on to the headphone stand.  The RS180 requires you to press a button on the base for a second and one on the headset for a second.  On the plus side the RS180 does not hit you with eye popping static when the sound signal on the TV is not present when a movie is paused for a few seconds.  Overall, the upgrade to the RS180 was worth it, the digital sound quality is great.  I daisy chained the old RS120 base off the RS180 base for a second headset for another evening viewer when needed.
