sg5
VI have a pair of Sennheiser HD 580's that are wired, and I keep tripping over & tearing the wires. I've replaced 3 sets already and to top it off, I sat on them awhile back and broke the headband. It was time to go shopping for a new pair. I researched wireless and chose these due to the KLEER technology, the ratings and the ability to mate up to 4 pair to the base. Another great feature is the audio pass through port, so I don't have to tie up another audio out from my devices. I am hard of hearing and am always struggling to understand TV dialogue, but with these on, vocals are crystal clear and I no longer need to turn on closed captions. These cans are extremely quiet, I have not experienced any background noise at all and am able to roam around the house freely with no drop in sound quality. They play way too loud for me, so I've not turned them up as far as they will go. Sound great with music and have a very natural sound. If you are into OTT bass response, aka BEATS, these are not for you. If you like music the way it SHOULD be heard, then I recommend these.
