VHaving had mixed experiences with wireless headphones in the past (including an older set of Sennheisers), I was a little skeptical when I ordered these. However, I am very happy with them. The set-up is dead easy, the sound is terrific, they are comfortable to wear.My only quibble is with the range. I used these first in an office environment with a very open floorplan. I didn't have the chance to test the full '300 range claimed, but I never had any dropouts. I recently brought these home, and the experience is a little different. Our house is a bi-level that is '48 long. The headset transmitted is on the lower level at one end, and the signal doesn't reach reliably to the bedroom on the upper floor at the other end. To be fair, we have two wireless networks as well as cordless phones so it might be an interference issue. But if you are planning to try these for roaming all around a big house you might have problems.But when you are in range, the sound is really terrific, with no hiss or interference. They really do sound like a good set of wired phones.
