VOutstanding Performance
p2297
sg5
VI have trouble listening to TV or Movies when sound levels are set to 'normal'. My preferred listening mode is set at above normal. This of course causes audio problems for others. Investigating into wireless sound transmission led me to Sennheiser and their wares and the RS 180 Digital Wireless Headphone System is my answer. The ouput and sound amplification is about as good as can be and the audio-out connections from the source are simple.The quick reference guide booklet is a bit short but all needed info is found on the supplied CD. My receiver is not the latest so I had to wire into the TV Audio Out to the RS 180 Transmitter and its output to my receiver. All necessary wires are supplied and all works perfectly. The reception works all through the house which is all I need. The ear pads do get a little warm but they are comfortable. The controls leave something to be desired, too tiny and I'm sure Sennheiser will address this in later models. For what this system does for me, I would highly recommend the RS 180.
