VThese wireless headphones are extremely comfortable and the sound quality is excellent. They're well worth the price.I ended up getting two pairs, one for me and one for my spouse. And that's where they lost their fifth star. Two sets of headphones with two base stations doesn't work perfectly all the time. Once in a while, the signals will get confused; suddenly I'll be hearing her base station's signal and she'll be hearing mine. Or sometimes my base station will "take over" and we'll both hear it. Or hers will.Resyncing the headphones to base stations is fairly awkward, too. You have to hold down the power buttons on both, wait a few minutes, and hope it all worked out right. It would be easier if there was a "sync" button or something.Overall, I'm very happy with these. I can live with the occasional glitch for the comfort and quality they offer otherwise. Would buy again.
